OL,3,CAnger of families who paid thousands
OL,4,Cfor non-existent funeral plans
OL,6,FWhile Mr Colby's funeral went ahead as
OL,7,Fplanned last year, when Mrs Colby
OL,8,Fcontacted third-party provider
OL,9,FEcclesiastical Planning Services she
OL,10,Fwas told there was no record of her
OL,11,Fpre-paid policy.JMrs Colby said: "I
OL,12,Fasked if it could be in just my
OL,13,Fhusband's name and she came back again
OL,14,Fand said there was nothing at all. It
OL,15,Fwas very hard because you get over
OL,16,Fyour main bereavement and then it's
OL,17,Flike it's all starting again."
