OL,3,CAnger of families who paid thousands
OL,4,Cfor non-existent funeral plans
OL,6,FThey were given official-looking
OL,7,Fdocuments, but were later told the
OL,8,Fplan did not exist.JMs Rollinson said
OL,9,Fshe was "very angry".JMr Richards
OL,10,Fsaid: "I feel I've got some years left
OL,11,Fin me but I don't really want to be
OL,12,Fworrying over financial issues at my
OL,13,Fage."JEcclesiastical Planning
OL,14,FServices. In a statement they said
OL,15,F"This is a deeply distressing incident
OL,16,Ffor the families affected. We are not
OL,17,Fable to comment on individual cases.
OL,18,FHumberside police have asked anyone
OL,19,Fwho is concerned about fraudulent
OL,20,Factivity to contact them directly."
OL,21,FMore than 2,000 calls have been made
OL,22,Fto a special helpline set up by
OL,23,FHumberside Police for families
OL,24,Fconcerned about their involvement with
OL,25,FLegacy.
